{"type":"text","timestamp":1776634702618,"sessionID":"ses_2585224bcffeFuyItcg68twIfN","part":{"id":"prt_da7ae2b15001VeQBoH2MlNamBm","messageID":"msg_da7ae1f8e001cOM3G6LKq0OrBZ","sessionID":"ses_2585224bcffeFuyItcg68twIfN","type":"text","text":"\n\n**Neovim** is a refactored fork of Vim, designed to be more maintainable, extensible, and with better modern UIs. Here are the key points:\n\n- **Goal**: Aggressively refactor Vim to enable new features, improve UX, and simplify development\n- **Language**: Written in C with Lua for configuration/plugins (not Vimscript)\n- **API**: First-class API access via msgpack-RPC, callable from multiple languages (Python, Ruby, Go, etc.)\n- **Plugins**: Load remote plugins from any language; configuration in Lua\n- **Embedded**: Built-in terminal emulator, runs in terminal or connected to external UIs\n- **Version**: Latest is v0.11.4\n\nKey architectural differences from Vim:\n- Uses Lua for plugins and config instead of Vimscript\n- Has a built-in RPC server for external UIs (like VSCode, desktop GUIs)\n- Supports modern UI protocols (since v0.10+ has DECSCA, DECFRA for rendering)\n- Extensive API for building custom UIs and integrations\n\nThe project was started around 2014 and now has ~5,900 code examples in its documentation with high source reputation.","time":{"start":1776634702613,"end":1776634702616}}}
